20on%20the%20situation%2C%20including%20that%20of%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20constitute%20a%20soliloquy%20of%20silence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20August%201947%2C%20in%20the%20aftermath%20of%20the%20horror%20of%20Hindu-Muslim%20Partition-era%20killings%2C%20the%20RSS%20had%20hoped%20%E2%80%93%20records%20of%20the%20period%20and%20scholarly%20writings%20show%20%E2%80%93%20to%20weaponise%20inflamed%20anti-Muslim%20feelings%2C%20and%20nursed%20the%20ambition%20to%20take%20a%20hold%20over%20power.%20The%20post-colonial%20Indian%20state%20was%20in%20its%20infancy.%20A%20putsch%20was%20in%20the%20minds%20of%20men.%20But%20they%20had%20not%20reckoned%20with%20the%20ideological%20sturdiness%20of%20the%20first%20prime%20minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20murder%20of%20Gandhi%20also%20inflamed%20public%20sentiment%20against%20the%20RSS.%20Much%20water%20has%20flowed%20down%20our%20rivers%20since%20then.%20It%20is%20the%20RSS%20followers%20who%20are%20now%20in%20the%20saddle.%20The%20ideological%20inflection%20point%20is%20once%20again%20here.%20How%20will%20India%20respond%20as%20we%20approach%20our%2076th%20Independence%20Day%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fanand-k-sahay%5C%22%3EAnand%20K.%20Sahay%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20journalist%20and%20political%20commentator%20based%20in%20New%20Delhi.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692018843000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F03%2F28144222%2FIMG_0206.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fsetting-of-the-ideological-stage-before-the-election%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22For%20the%20past%20ten%20years%2C%20the%20followers%20of%20the%20RSS%20have%20enjoyed%20practically%20untrammelled%20state%20power.%20And%20it%20is%20this%20which%20is%20now%20their%20aim%20to%20extend%20%E2%80%93%20at%20any%20price.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire