2%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Caste%E2%80%99s%20Role%20in%20Shaping%20Water%20Access%20Is%20Missing%20From%20Indian%20Environmental%20Discourse%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F14154839%2FThar_Desert_India_Water_well.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20independence-eve%20this%20year%20marks%20the%20death%20of%20little%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fother-states%2Fdalit-boy-dies-after-being-assaulted-by-teacher-in-rajasthan-school%2Farticle65766467.ece%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EIndra%20Meghwal%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20a%20nine-year-old%20Dalit%20boy%20beaten%20to%20death%20by%20his%20%E2%80%98upper%20caste%E2%80%99%20teacher%20in%20Jalore%20district%20of%20Rajasthan.%20Indra%20was%20thrashed%20to%20death%20because%20he%20drank%20water%20from%20a%20pot%20meant%20for%20his%20upper-caste%20teacher.%20His%20murder%20is%20not%20an%20isolated%20incident.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDalit%20students%20continue%20to%20endure%20violence%20and%20discrimination%20for%20drinking%20water%20in%20schools%20across%20India.%20Here%20are%20some%20widely%20reported%20incidents%20after%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3EIndra%E2%80%99s%20murder.%20On%20February%2012%2C%202023%2C%20a%20sixteen-year-old%20Dalit%20boy%20from%20Uttar%20Pradesh%E2%80%99s%20Sirwasuchand%20village%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fcities%2Flucknow%2Fdalit-student-beaten-up-drinking-water-from-principal-bottle-bijnor-3-booked-8442502%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EBijnor%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20was%20beaten%20by%20his%20principal%20for%20drinking%20the%20water%20from%20his%20bottle.%20In%20March%202023%2C%20another%20nine-year-old%20Dalit%20child%20from%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.siasat.com%2Fup-9-year-old-dalit-boy-thrashed-by-teacher-for-drinking-water-2553554%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EJalaun%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20district%20of%20UP%20was%20thrashed%20by%20a%20teacher%20for%20drinking%20water%20from%20a%20pond.%20In%20July%202023%2C%20a%20Dalit%20boy%20of%20Rajasthan%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fzeenews.india.com%2Fhindi%2Findia%2Fdalit-student-allegedly-beaten-by-teacher-in-rajasthan-barmer-for-drinking-water-from-pot%2F1769709%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ENetrad%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20village%20(Barmer%20district)%20was%20physically%20abused%20by%20his%20school%20teacher%20for%20drinking%20water%20from%20the%20school%20pot.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EUntouchability%20was%20legally%20abolished%20by%20the%20Indian%20constitution%20over%20seven%20decades%20back.%20The%20Prevention%20of%20Atrocities%20Act%20of%201989%20(%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftribal.nic.in%2FactRules%2FpreventionofAtricities.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ESC%2FST%20PoA%2C%201989%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E)%20is%20supposed%20to%20provide%20further%20safeguards%20against%20attacks%20like%20the%20one%20that%20killed%20Indra%20Meghwal.%20Why%20then%20does%20access%20to%20drinking%20water%20continue%20to%20be%20the%20site%20of%20some%20of%20the%20worst%20caste%20atrocities%20nearly%20a%20century%20after%20Dr%20B.R.%20Ambedkar%20led%20the%20Mahad%20Satyagraha%20in%201927%3F%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDespite%20the%20alarming%20regularity%20with%20which%20caste%20atrocity%20incidents%20related%20to%20water%20access%20occur%2C%20the%20social%20and%20environmental%20discourse%20in%20India%20has%20largely%20rendered%20caste%20invisible%20in%20discussions%20about%20water.%20Caste%20continues%20to%20be%20a%20%E2%80%9C%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fopinion%2Fcolumns%2Fcaste-and-access-to-water-the-missing-link-jal-jeevan-mission-8396750%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThe%2520study%2520found%2520that%252072%2Cfor%2520%25E2%2580%259Caccess%2520to%2520water%25E2%2580%259D.%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Emissing%20link%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%9C%3Cspan%3E.%20Scholars%20like%20Mukul%20Sharma%20have%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.berghahnjournals.com%2Fview%2Fjournals%2Fenvironment-and-society%2F13%2F1%2Fares130106.xml%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eshown%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20how%20caste%20is%20not%20central%20to%20the%20environmental%20discourse%20even%20when%20justice%20is%20ostensibly%20the%20primary%20field%20of%20inquiry.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EQuestions%20of%20purity-pollution%20or%20%E2%80%98division%20of%20labourers%E2%80%99%20rather%20than%20division%20of%20labour%20%E2%80%93%20the%20constitutive%20features%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20caste%20hierarchy%20%E2%80%93%20remain%20outside%20the%20pale%20of%20environmental%20and%20water%20discourse%20in%20India.%20A%20principal%20reason%20for%20this%20neglect%20is%20that%20Indian%20environmental%20studies%20(including%20water)%20are%20dominated%20by%20upper-caste%20scholars%2C%20researchers%2C%20and%20academics%20with%20little%20or%20no%20lived%20experience%20of%20how%20the%20Bahujan%20masses%20of%20India%20experience%20water%20and%20the%20environment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20crisis%20of%20Bahujan%20exclusion%20is%20why%20we%20can%20wax%20eloquent%20about%20water%20access%20being%20a%20fundamental%20human%20right%20while%20neglecting%20how%20caste%20is%20the%20single%20most%20important%20barrier%20to%20the%20actual%20realisation%20of%20this%20fundamental%20right.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20invisibilisation%20of%20caste%20in%20the%20discussion%20around%20water%20access%20is%20at%20the%20root%20of%20how%20water%20conundrums%20in%20India%20are%20reduced%20to%20a%20technocratic%20discourse.%20At%20best%2C%20this%20discourse%20engages%20with%20the%20physical%2C%20hydrological%20cycle%20that%20is%20conceived%20as%20being%20independent%20of%20social%2C%20political%2C%20and%20economic%20influences.%20The%20water%20cycle%20from%20our%20elementary%20school%20textbooks%20introduces%20the%20hydrological%20cycle%20with%20a%20pretty%20picture%20of%20the%20sun%2C%20clouds%2C%20mountains%2C%20rivers%2C%20lakes%2C%20and%20oceans%20along%20with%20the%20process%20of%20evaporation%2C%20transpiration%2C%20condensation%2C%20precipitation%2C%20and%20sometimes%20even%20groundwater.%20None%20of%20the%20Indian%20textbooks%2C%20however%2C%20have%20people%20depicted%20in%20this%20introduction%20to%20the%20water%20cycle.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F14161509%2FDiagram_of_the_Water_Cycle.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F14161509%2FDiagram_of_the_Water_Cycle.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F14161509%2FDiagram_of_the_Water_Cycle-300x188.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F14161509%2FDiagram_of_the_Water_Cycle-1024x640.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-668058%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22750%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20diagram%20of%20the%20water%20cycle.%20Photo%3A%20Ehud%20Tal%2FWikimedia%20Commons%2C%20CC%20BY-SA%204.0%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20have%20a%20water%20crisis%20because%20this%20%E2%80%98pristine%E2%80%99%20picture%20has%20been%20modified%20and%20stressed%20by%20the%20human%20economy%20and%20society.%20Across%20town%20and%20country%2C%20people%20%E2%80%98live-work-play%E2%80%99%20by%20interfering%20with%20the%20physical%20water%20cycle.%20For%20example%2C%20Bengaluru%2C%20where%20I%20am%20currently%20based%2C%20imports%20nearly%20as%20much%20river%20water%20in%20a%20year%20from%20a%20river%20source%20a%20hundred%20kilometres%20away%20as%20the%20city%20receives%20in%20the%20form%20of%20rainfall.%20Add%20in%20all%20the%20groundwater%20that%20is%20extracted%20and%20the%20waste%20flows%20back%20to%20the%20environment.%20The%20human%20influence%20on%20the%20overall%20hydrological%20cycle%20dwarfs%20the%20physical%20cycle.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Indian%20environmental%20discourse%20is%20not%20able%20to%20adequately%20characterise%20the%20human%20influence%20on%20the%20hydrological%20cycle%20because%20people%20cannot%20be%20disembodied%20from%20the%20deeply%20hierarchical%20caste%20structure%20that%20actually%20modulates%20human-water%20interactions%20in%20India.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EConfront%20the%20C%20word%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20cannot%20get%20serious%20about%20justice%20and%20sustainability%20(%E2%80%98justainability%E2%80%99)%20questions%20surrounding%20water%20in%20India%20unless%20we%20also%20confront%20the%20%E2%80%98C%E2%80%99%20word.%20Caste%20is%20at%20the%20front%20and%20centre%20of%20our%20water%20predicaments.%20If%20we%20did%20this%2C%20we%20will%20begin%20to%20understand%20how%20Dalits%2C%20Adivasis%20and%20other%20marginalised%20groups%20endure%20injustice%20at%20every%20point%20in%20the%20water%20cycle.%20In%20a%20recent%20study%2C%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Faltlawforum.org%2Fsumanto-mondal-caste-lines-in-bengaluru-settled-outside-the-pecking-order%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ECaste%20Lines%20in%20Bengaluru%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%99%2C%20researcher%20Sumanto%20Mondal%20studied%20the%20nexus%20between%20topography%20and%20caste.%20Mondal%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fearth.google.com%2Fweb%2F%4012.97238416%2C77.59532811%2C929.49766178a%2C33734.69078102d%2C30y%2C0h%2C0t%2C0r%2Fdata%3DMikKJwolCiExOHU4b0kxLXdpUjR3UTgzVDdlLU5OLW03a0gwZUs3Zl8gAQ%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EMapping%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20shows%20most%20of%20the%20highest%20elevation%20grounds%20in%20Bangalore%20are%20captured%20by%20the%20upper%20caste%20elite%20groups%20while%20a%20considerable%20number%20of%20lowered%20caste%20groups%20have%20been%20moved%20to%20low-lying%20areas.%20Such%20topographic%20inequality%20quite%20literally%20defines%20the%20contours%20of%20the%20hydrological%20cycle.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EResidents%20of%20low-lying%20areas%20are%20more%20vulnerable%20to%20natural%20hazards%20like%20flooding%20(that%20will%20increase%20in%20frequency%20and%20intensity%20on%20a%20warming%20planet).%20Building%20urban%20flood%20resilience%20cannot%20be%20accomplished%20unless%20we%20also%20ask%20the%20question%20of%20why%20the%20topographic%20maps%20in%20Indian%20towns%20and%20villages%20are%20congruent%20with%20the%20caste%20hierarchy.%20However%2C%20this%20is%20a%20question%20that%20is%20seldom%20asked%20by%20the%20extant%20environmental%20scholarship%20in%20India%2C%20let%20alone%20the%20official%20flood%20resilience%20bureaucratese.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECaste%20is%20a%20direct%20%E2%80%98natural%20hazard%E2%80%99%20for%20Dalits%20that%20follows%20and%20hunts%20them%20in%20the%20city%20as%20it%20does%20in%20the%20country.%20As%20reported%20by%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fkarnataka%2Fthree-arrested-in-alleged-caste-based-double-murder%2Farticle66843300.ece%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20in%20May%202023%2C%20two%20Dalit%20youths%20were%20murdered%20by%20upper-caste%20men%20in%20Rajanakunte%20on%20the%20outskirts%20of%20Bengaluru.%20They%20had%20trespassed%20their%20caste%20location%20by%20drinking%20water%20from%20a%20water%20jar%20reserved%20for%20upper%20castes%20at%20a%20hotel%20in%20Hesarghatta.%20The%20%E2%80%98flow%E2%80%99%20of%20caste%20is%20indistinguishable%20from%20how%20water%20flows%20through%20the%20hydrological%20cycle.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAmbedkar%20famously%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fccnmtl.columbia.edu%2Fprojects%2Fmmt%2Fambedkar%2Fweb%2Fsection_5.html%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eargued%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20water%20is%20central%20to%20maintaining%20the%20boundary%20between%20the%20%E2%80%98touchables%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98untouchables%E2%80%99.%20Policing%20and%20maintaining%20this%20boundary%20is%20the%20source%20of%20violent%20persecution%20faced%20by%20Dalits%20and%20Adivasis%20in%20India.%20According%20to%20the%20National%20Crime%20Records%20Bureau%20(NCRB)%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcjp.org.in%2F2022-a-look-back-at-hate-crimes-against-dalits-and-adivasis%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DUttar%2520Pradesh%2520(13%252C146%2520cases)%2520reported%2COdisha%25204.5%2525%2520(2%252C327)%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EReport%20of%202021%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20the%20atrocities%20against%20Scheduled%20Castes%20(SC)%20and%20Scheduled%20Tribes%20(ST)%20have%20increased%20by%201.2%25%20and%206.4%25%20respectively.%20Further%2C%20the%20report%20shows%20how%20most%20of%20the%20caste%20atrocities%20against%20SC%2FSTs%20are%20related%20to%20conflicts%20over%20access%20to%20drinking%20water%20sources.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.unesco.org%2Fen%2Farticles%2Fgroundwater-making-invisible-visible-2022-and-beyond%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%98Groundwater%3A%20Making%20the%20Invisible%20Visible%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20was%20the%20theme%20chosen%20for%20the%202022%20UN%20world%20water%20day.%20Many%20Indian%20environmental%20scholars%20and%20activists%20enthusiastically%20participated%20in%20this%20effort.%20Indian%20upper%20caste%20environmental%20discourse%20has%20always%20been%20engaged%20with%20the%20questions%20of%20%E2%80%98where%20does%20your%20water%20come%20from%20and%20where%20does%20your%20wastewater%20go%E2%80%99.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESadly%2C%20the%20upper%20castes%20have%20never%20troubled%20themselves%20to%20ask%20the%20question%20%E2%80%98who%20brings%20the%20water%E2%80%99%20or%20%E2%80%98who%20handles%E2%80%99%20wastewater%20infrastructure.%20The%20privilege%20of%20their%20birth-based%20identities%2C%20%E2%80%98their%20caste%E2%80%99%2C%20has%20shielded%20them%20from%20the%20lived%20experiences%20of%20Dalits%20and%20marginalised%20people.%20Groundwater%2C%20or%20any%20water%20in%20India%20will%20remain%20invisible%20unless%20the%20water%20and%20sanitation%20discourse%20shuns%20its%20ostrich-like%20response%20to%20the%20very%20mention%20of%20caste.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIgnoring%20caste%20not%20an%20option%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20a%20Dalit%20who%20is%20engaged%20professionally%20in%20managing%20water%20resources%2C%20ignoring%20the%20shadow%20that%20caste%20casts%20on%20the%20hydrological%20cycle%20is%20not%20an%20option%20for%20me.%20My%20life%20cycle%20has%20been%20punctuated%20by%20a%20constant%20struggle%20with%20the%20water%20cycle.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20my%20mother%20was%20pregnant%20with%20my%20sister%2C%20she%20still%20had%20to%20struggle%20to%20collect%20water%20for%20the%20household%20in%20Siddharth%20Nagar%20(a%20Dalit%20Colony%20in%20Nanded%2C%20Maharashtra).%20I%20have%20enduring%20memories%20of%20making%20numerous%20rounds%20on%20my%20father%E2%80%99s%20bike%20to%20fetch%20water%20from%20public%20handpumps.%20This%20means%20that%20I%20often%20had%20to%20skip%20schoolwork.%20Summers%20only%20made%20it%20worse.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%C2%A0If%20you%20could%20not%20climb%20on%20top%20of%20the%20municipal%20tankers%20and%20threw%20in%20a%20pipe%20to%20draw%20water%2C%20the%20household%20would%20have%20to%20go%20thirsty.%20The%20bike%20trips%20also%20became%20more%20frequent%20as%20the%20water%20tables%20dipped.%20Water%20conservation%20was%20second%20nature%20for%20Dalit%20children%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0unlike%20upper%20caste%20children%20who%20had%20bountiful%20piped%20water%20and%20private%20tankers%20filling%20up%20their%20large%20stockpiles.%20Water%20has%20never%20been%20invisible%20for%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Einvisibilised%20people%20like%20me.%20Unarguably%2C%20the%20most%20invisibilised%20are%20the%20manual%20scavengers%20of%20independent%20India.%20When%20floods%20hit%20the%20cities%20and%20block%20key%20city%20infrastructure%20including%20sewers%2C%20these%20%E2%80%98invisible%E2%80%99%20manual%20scavengers%20risk%20their%20lives%20to%20keep%20the%20cities%20functioning.%20While%20the%20news%20of%20their%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thequint.com%2Fquintlab%2Fhellhole-reality-of-manual-scavenging-in-india%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Edeaths%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20has%20been%20visible%2C%20their%20existence%20still%20has%20been%20invisibilised%20by%20the%20upper%20caste%20%E2%80%98water%20cycle%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20cloak%20of%20invisibility%20amongst%20Indian%20environmentalists%20and%20academic%20researchers%20against%20caste%20remains%20the%20most%20significant%20gap%20between%20the%20%E2%80%98technical%E2%80%99%20and%20%E2%80%98social%E2%80%99%20disciplinary%20boundaries.%20Recent%20efforts%20(for%20example%20by%20Ambika%20Aiyadurai%20and%20her%20lab)%20have%20called%20for%20a%20reimagination%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epw.in%2Fjournal%2F2023%2F31%2Falternative-standpoint%2Fenvironmental-humanities%25C2%25A0-way-forward.html%3F0%3Dip_login_no_cache%253Da45367f325ae9bfebfa1da7606fe6360%23%3A~%3Atext%3DTo%2520that%2520end%252C%2520environmental%2520humanities%2Crigid%2520social%2520structures%2520of%2520society.%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ehuman-environment%E2%80%99%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20relationship.%20Brahminical%20and%20men-centric%20dominance%20in%20the%20ecological%20worldviews%20act%20as%20a%20barrier%20and%20block%20the%20perspectives%20of%20Dalits%20and%20marginalised%20people%20from%20taking%20centre%20stage%20in%20the%20pedagogical%20definition%20of%20environment%20in%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20academic%2C%20non-academic%2C%20and%20policy%20forums.%20Upper%20caste%20calls%20for%20transcending%20disciplinary%20boundaries%20will%20remain%20unfulfilled%20unless%20we%20recognise%20caste%20as%20the%20glue%20that%20binds%20the%20physical%20and%20the%20social.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20constitutive%20linkages%20between%20caste%20and%20the%20water%20cycle%20have%20to%20be%20understood%20to%20actually%20ensure%20human%20dignity%20and%20equal%20rights%20of%20access%20to%20water%20for%20every%20individual%20in%20India.%20Evaporation%20provides%20a%20temporary%20escape%20from%20the%20wretchedness%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20caste%20society%20%E2%80%93%20only%20to%20fall%20back%20after%20condensation.%20However%2C%20for%20Dalits%20and%20other%20marginalised%20groups%2C%20there%20is%20not%20even%20this%20periodic%20respite.%20Unless%20we%20recognise%20how%20the%20Indian%20hydrological%20cycles%20are%20embedded%20in%20caste%2C%20the%20water%20cycle%20will%20remain%20broken%20for%20the%20broken%20(Dalits)%20of%20India.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20author%20is%20an%20independent%20researcher%20based%20in%20Bengaluru.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692013821000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F14154839%2FThar_Desert_India_Water_well.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fcaste-water-access-missing-india-environmental-discourse%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Even%20as%20environmentalists%20and%20researchers%20wax%20eloquent%20about%20water%20access%20being%20a%20fundamental%20human%20right%2C%20they%20neglect%20the%20fact%20that%20caste%20is%20the%20single%20most%20important%20barrier%20to%20the%20actual%20realisation%20of%20this%20fundamental%20right.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcaste%2Fcaste-water-access-missing-india-environmental-discourse%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Watch%3A%20Rohit's%20hilarious%20take%20on%20facing%20these%20pacers%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692013745000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-102725737%2Cimgsize-34690.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fsports%2Fcricket%2Fnews%2Fwatch-what-rohit-sharma-has-to-say-about-facing-these-fast-bowlers%2Farticleshow%2F102725732.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22India%20skipper%20Rohit%20Sharma's%20ability%20to%20dismantle%20fast%20bowlers%20with%20his%20impeccable%20timing%20and%20sublime%20technique%20is%20known%20in%20the%20cricketing%20arena.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TIMESOFINDIA.COM%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A18%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fsports%2Fcricket%2Fnews%2Fwatch-what-rohit-sharma-has-to-say-about-facing-these-fast-bowlers%2Farticleshow%2F102725732.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Abhishek%20was%20to%20debut%20alongside%20Dilip%20Kumar%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692013133000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-102725395%2Cimgsize-40154.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fentertainment%2Fhindi%2Fbollywood%2Fnews%2Fabhishek-bachchan-was-to-debut-alongside-dilip-kumar-in-1998-says-it-never-got-made-exclusive%2Farticleshow%2F102725166.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F102725166.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EDirected%20by%20R%20Balki%2C%20'Ghoomer'%20stars%20Ab