.%20And%20crucially%2C%20many%20of%20the%20jobs%20that%20will%20be%20lost%20will%20be%20replaced%20by%20new%20ones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20crescendo%20for%20this%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ft.com%2Fcontent%2F64c33d29-7c76-40bf-8a88-c4b3afea26de%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etechnological%20wave%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20surging%2C%20and%20we%20are%20at%20just%20the%20beginning%20of%20this%20upheaval%20that%20will%20ripple%20through%20the%20labor%20market%20and%20global%20economy.%20It's%20likely%20to%20be%20a%20transformation%20as%20influential%20as%20the%20industrial%20revolution%20and%20the%20rise%20of%20the%20internet.%20The%20changes%20could%20boost%20living%20standards%2C%20improve%20productivity%2C%20and%20accelerate%20economic%20opportunities%2C%20but%20this%20rosy%20future%20is%20not%20guaranteed.%20Unless%20governments%2C%20CEOs%2C%20and%20workers%20properly%20prepare%20for%20the%20upsurge%20with%20urgency%2C%20the%20AI%20revolution%20could%20be%20painful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20didn't%20see%20the%20internet%20coming%2C%20but%20AI%20is%20within%20view%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20adoption%20of%20groundbreaking%20technology%20is%20often%20hard%20to%20predict.%20Take%20the%20internet%3A%20In%201995%2C%20Newsweek%20published%20an%20article%20titled%2C%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newsweek.com%2Fclifford-stoll-why-web-wont-be-nirvana-185306%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWhy%20the%20Web%20Won't%20Be%20Nirvana%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20making%20the%20case%20that%20books%20and%20airline%20tickets%20would%20never%20be%20purchased%20over%20the%20internet.%20Later%20that%20year%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3Dfs-YpQj88ew%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBill%20Gates%20was%20asked%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20an%20unconvinced%20David%20Letterman%2C%20%26quot%3BWhat%20about%20this%20internet%20thing%3F%26quot%3B%20Even%20three%20years%20later%2C%20as%20adoption%20grew%2C%20the%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpaul-krugman-responds-to-internet-quote-2013-12%5C%22%3E%20economist%20Paul%20Krugman%20famously%20declared%20that%20the%20internet's%20influence%3C%2Fa%3E%20would%20be%20no%20greater%20than%20that%20of%20the%20fax%20machine.%20In%20hindsight%2C%20it's%20clear%20that%20the%20internet's%20effects%20couldn't%20have%20been%20any%20more%20miscalculated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20the%20reason%20for%20the%20initial%20skepticism%20was%20that%20the%20influence%20of%20the%20internet%20was%20uneven%20and%20slow%20at%20first%20but%20quickly%20grew%20as%20more%20people%20learned%20how%20it%20worked.%20%26quot%3BThe%20rule%20for%20exponential%20curves%20is%20that%20they%20changed%20the%20world%20slowly%20at%20first%2C%20and%20then%20suddenly%2C%26quot%3B%20Erik%20Brynjolfsson%2C%20a%20Stanford%20University%20innovation%20economist%2C%20told%20me.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20arrival%20of%20AI%20presents%20similar%20unknowns%20%E2%80%94%20but%20the%20growth%20curve%20is%20becoming%20clear%20much%20quicker.%20In%202017%2C%20McKinsey%20estimated%20that%20robust%20large%20language%20models%20such%20as%20GPT-4%20would%20be%20developed%20by%202027.%20But%20they%20are%20already%20here.%20And%20seemingly%20overnight%2C%20OpenAI's%20generative%20AI%20was%20integrated%20into%20Microsoft%20products%2C%20and%20in%20the%20span%20of%20a%20few%20months%2C%20corporate%20giants%20including%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nytimes.com%2F2023%2F07%2F05%2Ftechnology%2Fbusiness-ai-technology.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAmazon%2C%20AT%26amp%3BT%2C%20Salesforce%2C%20and%20Cisco%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20rushed%20to%20incorporate%20enterprise-grade%20AI%20tools.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mckinsey.com%2Fcapabilities%2Fmckinsey-digital%2Four-insights%2Fthe-economic-potential-of-generative-AI-the-next-productivity-frontier%23key-insights%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMcKinsey's%20latest%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%20predicted%20that%20somewhere%20between%202030%20and%202060%2C%20half%20of%20today's%20work%20tasks%20would%20be%20automated.%20Their%20best%20guess%20as%20to%20when%20this%20will%20happen%20%E2%80%94%202045%20%E2%80%94%20is%20almost%20a%20decade%20earlier%20than%20previously%20estimated.%20Things%20are%20changing%20fast.And%20as%20adoption%20picks%20up%2C%20so%20will%20the%20downstream%20effects%20of%20the%20technology.%20The%20World%20Economic%20Forum%20estimated%2083%20million%20jobs%20worldwide%20would%20be%20lost%20over%20the%20next%20five%20years%20because%20of%20AI%2C%20with%2069%20million%20jobs%20created%20%E2%80%94%20that%20leaves%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.lemonde.fr%2Fen%2Feconomy%2Farticle%2F2023%2F05%2F03%2Fworld-economic-forum-estimates-14-million-net-job-losses-worldwide-by-2027_6025227_19.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E14%20million%20jobs%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20will%20cease%20to%20exist%20during%20that%20timeframe.%20Even%20the%20people%20who%20do%20retain%20their%20jobs%20will%20experience%20a%20massive%20shift%20in%20how%20they%20do%20their%20work%3A%20The%20World%20Economic%20Forum%20says%20that%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww3.weforum.org%2Fdocs%2FWEF_Future_of_Jobs_2023.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E44%25%20of%20workers'%20core%20skills%20are%20expected%20to%20change%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20next%20five%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cq%3EI%20do%20not%20think%20we'll%20see%20mass%20unemployment.%20But%20I%20do%20think%20we'll%20see%20mass%20disruption.%3C%2Fq%3E%20%3Ccite%3EStanford%20economist%20Erik%20Brynjolfsson%3C%2Fcite%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EPast%20automation%20technologies%20had%20the%20most%20effect%20on%20low-skilled%20workers.%20But%20with%20generative%20AI%2C%20the%20more%20educated%20and%20highly%20skilled%20workers%20who%20previously%20were%20immune%20to%20automation%20are%20vulnerable.%20According%20to%20the%20International%20Labor%20Organization%2C%20there%20are%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsdgs.un.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2023-05%2FB59%2520-%2520Berg%2520-%2520Automation%2520hits%2520the%2520knowledge%2520worker%2520ChatGPT%2520and%2520the%2520future%2520of%2520work.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ebetween%20644%20and%20997%20million%20knowledge%20workers%3C%2Fa%3E%20globally%2C%20between%2020%25%20and%2030%25%20of%20total%20global%20employment.%20In%20the%20US%2C%20the%20knowledge-worker%20class%20is%20estimated%20to%20be%20nearly%20100%20million%20workers%2C%20one%20out%20of%20three%20Americans.%20A%20broad%20spectrum%20of%20occupations%20%E2%80%94%20marketing%20and%20sales%2C%20software%20engineering%2C%20research%20and%20development%2C%20accounting%2C%20financial%20advising%2C%20and%20writing%2C%20to%20name%20a%20few%20%E2%80%94%20is%20at%20risk%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-jobs-at-risk-replacement-artificial-intelligence-ai-labor-trends-2023-02%5C%22%3Ebeing%20automated%20away%20or%20evolving%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20doesn't%20mean%2C%20however%2C%20that%20there%20will%20be%20a%20flood%20of%20unemployed%20workers%20begging%20for%20any%20job.%20AI%20will%20lead%20to%20net%20job%20creation%20over%20the%20long%20run%2C%20and%20some%20roles%20that%20seem%20like%20they%20will%20be%20affected%20may%20actually%20grow%20in%20demand.%20For%20instance%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Fautomation-can-actually-create-more-jobs-1481480200%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EATMs%20increased%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20number%20of%20bank%20tellers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20do%20not%20think%20we'll%20see%20mass%20unemployment%2C%26quot%3B%20Brynjolfsson%2C%20who%20anticipates%20AI%20spreading%20faster%20than%20other%20general-purpose%20technologies%2C%20told%20me.%20%26quot%3BBut%20I%20do%20think%20we'll%20see%20mass%20disruption%2C%20where%20a%20lot%20of%20wages%20for%20some%20jobs%20will%20fall%2C%20wages%20for%20other%20jobs%20will%20rise%2C%20and%20we'll%20be%20shifting%20around%20into%20demand%20for%20different%20kinds%20of%20skills.%20They'll%20have%20to%20be%20a%20lot%20of%20reallocation%20of%20labor%20and%20rescaling%20of%20labor%20with%20winners%20and%20losers.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20shift%20will%20be%20so%20massive%20that%20we%20won't%20miss%20many%20of%20the%20jobs%20that%20disappear.%20Before%20the%20industrial%20revolution%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.weforum.org%2Fagenda%2F2023%2F05%2Fjobs-lost-created-ai-gpt%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20job%20of%20a%20human%20alarm%20clock%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20to%20wake%20up%20workers%20in%20the%20early-morning%20hours%20by%20tapping%20a%20broomstick%20on%20their%20window.%20Thanks%20to%20alarm%20clocks%2C%20no%20one%20misses%20this%20job%20today.%20Similarly%20with%20AI%2C%20there%20will%20be%20jobs%20that%20will%20be%20conveniently%20forgotten%20about.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPermanent%20mass%20unemployment%20can%20safely%20be%20ruled%20out%2C%20but%20in%20the%20short%20term%2C%20the%20transition%20will%20be%20messy.%20If%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gspublishing.com%2Fcontent%2Fresearch%2Fen%2Freports%2F2023%2F03%2F27%2Fd64e052b-0f6e-45d7-967b-d7be35fabd16.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eone-quarter%20of%20tasks%20across%20all%20US%20occupations%3C%2Fa%3E%20were%20automated%20by%20AI%2C%20and%20one-third%20of%20workers'%20workload%20replaced%2C%20it%20would%20take%20only%20a%20small%20segment%20of%20the%20broad%20white-collar%20class%20to%20simultaneously%20experience%20job%20losses%20or%20transitions%20for%20it%20to%20have%20a%20dire%20impact%20on%20the%20broader%20economy.%20This%20sort%20of%20monumental%20reshuffling%20requires%20preparation%20on%20the%20part%20of%20governments%20and%20businesses.%20In%20its%20most%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.oecd.org%2Femployment-outlook%2F2023%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erecent%20employment%20outlook%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20Organization%20for%20Economic%20Co-operation%20and%20Development%20declared%20that%20this%20AI%20revolution%20was%20creating%20%26quot%3Ban%20urgent%20need%20to%20act%20now%26quot%3B%20to%20help%20the%20economy%20adapt.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EProductivity%20boom%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EIn%201987%2C%20the%20economist%20Robert%20Solow%20famously%20declared%3A%20%26quot%3BYou%20can%20see%20the%20computer%20age%20everywhere%20but%20in%20the%20productivity%20statistics.%26quot%3B%20Solow's%20%26quot%3Bproductivity%20paradox%26quot%3B%20spotlighted%20a%20key%20puzzle%20of%20the%20emerging%20computer%20age.%20Even%20with%20heavy%20investments%20in%20information%20technology%20and%20computing%20%E2%80%94%20which%20were%20supposedly%20making%20workers%20more%20productive%20%E2%80%94%20official%20statistics%20showed%20that%20workers%20were%20not%20producing%20more%20per%20hour.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERobert%20Gordon%2C%20a%20macroeconomist%20and%20self-styled%20%26quot%3B%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.imf.org%2Fexternal%2Fpubs%2Fft%2Ffandd%2F2017%2F06%2Fpeople.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprophet%20of%20pessimism%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%26quot%3B%20provocatively%20suggested%20that%20the%20ho-hum%20productivity%20figures%20proved%20that%20new%20technology%20today%20was%20less%20radical%20than%20in%20the%20past%20and%20that%20as%20a%20result%2C%20the%20world's%20advanced%20economies%20had%20entered%20a%20point%20of%20stagnation.%20The%20most%20impactful%20technologies%20%E2%80%94%20the%20car%2C%20the%20toilet%20%E2%80%94%20have%20already%20been%20invented%2C%20he%20argued%2C%20and%20everything%20else%20only%20incrementally%20improves%20productivity.%20Along%20the%20same%20lines%2C%20other%20economists%20have%20suggested%20that%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fideas.repec.org%2Fa%2Faea%2Faecrev%2Fv110y2020i4p1104-44.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20growth%20rate%20of%20new%20ideas%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20slowing.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22raw%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FtLCWd%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Labor%20productivity%20growth%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22450%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20arguments%20may%20seem%20like%20a%20compelling%20reason%20to%20doubt%20the%20productivity%20gains%20of%20AI%20at%20first%2C%20but%20there's%20good%20reason%20to%20think%20that%20the%20latest%20revolution%20could%20produce%20more%20rapid%20gains.%20The%20internet's%20mass%20adoption%20required%20software%2C%20network%20protocols%2C%20infrastructure%2C%20and%20devices%20%E2%80%94%20it%20took%20awhile%20for%20every%20home%20and%20office%20to%20have%20computers%20and%20internet%20access.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EToday%2C%20AI's%20adoption%20could%20happen%20much%20faster%20since%20the%20technological%20infrastructure%20is%20already%20in%20place.%20Plus%2C%20in%20contrast%20to%20hype%20cycles%20around%20crypto%20or%20the%20metaverse%2C%20AI%20is%20entering%20maturity.%20Its%20user%20experience%20makes%20it%20uncomplicated%2C%20and%20it%20already%20has%20practical%20uses%2C%20which%20is%20why%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fchatgpt-secret-productivity-work-ai-technology-ban-employees-coworkers-job-2023-8%3Futm_medium%3Dnewsletter%26email%3Demil%2540capitolfoundry.com%26x%3De40353e92b59624ed6df11658967c6b058f9b249be72afb1c251ae610a446866%26utm_source%3DSailthru%26utm_campaign%3DInsider%2520Today%252C%2520August%25201%252C%25202023%26utm_term%3DINSIDER%2520TODAY%2520SEND%2520LIST%2520-%2520ALL%2520ENGAGED%5C%22%3Ehundreds%20of%20millions%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20people%20are%20already%20integrating%20the%20tech%20into%20their%20day-to-day%20workflows.%20This%20is%20starting%20to%20push%20the%20technology%20into%20companies.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20also%20not%20AI%20on%20its%20own%20that's%20game-changing%3B%20layering%20AI%20on%20top%20of%20preexisting%20tech%20can%20unlock%20exponential%20gains%20%E2%80%94%20just%20as%20the%20combination%20of%20the%20internet%2C%20GPS%20technology%2C%20and%20smartphones%20changed%20our%20world.%20Laser%20weeders%20that%20use%20AI%2C%20GPS%2C%20and%20tractor%20technology%20can%20now%20comb%20through%20crop%20fields%20in%20seconds%20to%20zap%20weeds%2C%20eliminating%20the%20need%20for%20herbicides%20or%20large%20hand-weeding%20crews.%20And%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Farticles%2F2023-07-07%2Fai-offers-key-information-for-treating-brain-cancer-study-finds%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAI%20embedded%20within%20advanced%20imaging%20tools%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20the%20potential%20to%20diagnose%20and%20treat%20cancer.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20internet%20made%20the%20world%20flat%2C%20then%20AI%20makes%20the%20world%20faster.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nber.org%2Fpapers%2Fw31161%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EOne%20recent%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20conducted%20by%20Brynjolfsson%20and%20his%20colleagues%20quantified%20the%20productivity%20of%20over%205%2C000%20customer-service%20agents%20who%20used%20generative-AI%20technology.%20The%20results%20were%20encouraging%3A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nber.org%2Fpapers%2Fw31161%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECall-center%20operators%20became%2014%25%20more%20productive%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20less%20experienced%20workers%20improved%20their%20productivity%20as%20much%20as%2030%25.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farxiv.org%2Fpdf%2F2302.06590.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EA%20study%20out%20of%20MIT%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20software%20developers%20completed%20tasks%2056%25%20faster%20with%20generative-code-completion%20software%2C%20and%20yet%20another%20study%20found%20that%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.science.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1126%2Fscience.adh2586%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eprofessional-document%20writing%20was%2040%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20faster%20using%20generative%20AI.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20small%20and%20large%20compounding%20effects%20of%20productivity%20growth%20across%20many%20industries%20are%20central%20to%20the%20growth%20trajectory%20and%20the%20long-run%20effects%20of%20AI.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gspublishing.com%2Fcontent%2Fresearch%2Fen%2Freports%2F2023%2F03%2F27%2Fd64e052b-0f6e-45d7-967b-d7be35fabd16.html%23_6098fc24-4737-4000-a842-6d1cb2bdd000%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGoldman%20Sachs%20estimated%20that%20over%2010%20years%2C%20generative%20AI%3C%2Fa%3E%20alone%20could%20raise%20annual%20US%20labor-productivity%20growth%20by%20just%20under%201.5%20percentage%20points%2C%20%26quot%3Broughly%20the%20same-sized%20boost%20that%20followed%20the%20emergence%20of%20prior%20transformative%20technologies%20like%20the%20electric%20motor%20and%20personal%20computer.%26quot%3B%20If%20that%20proved%20true%2C%20it%20would%20lead%20to%20an%20annual%20increase%20of%207%25%20in%20global%20GDP%2C%20while%20contributing%20%242.6%20trillion%20to%204.4%20trillion%20to%20the%20global%20economy%20%E2%80%94%20about%20the%20equivalent%20of%20the%20UK%20economy.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBrynjolfsson%2C%20a%20%26quot%3Bmindful%20optimist%2C%26quot%3B%20is%20confident%20that%20these%20productivity%20gains%20will%20accumulate%20%E2%80%94%20and%20show%20up%20in%20the%20official%20stats.%20He%20told%20me%20that%20he%20had%20a%20bet%20with%20Gordon%2C%20the%20pessimist%2C%20that%20productivity%20growth%20over%20the%20coming%20years%20would%20outpace%20the%201.4%25%20annual%20growth%20projected%20by%20the%20Congressional%20Budget%20Office.%20%26quot%3BIn%20fact%2C%20I%20think%20it's%20going%20to%20be%20closer%20to%20double%20that%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22raw%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FimrTi%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Aggregate%20labor%20productivity%20growth%20range%20based%20on%20adoption%20and%20capabilities%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22433%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20estimates%20for%20productivity%20reflect%20how%20workers%20within%20firms%20will%20become%20more%20efficient%20at%20their%20jobs%2C%20it%20also%20assumes%20that%20laid-off%20workers%20will%20find%20new%20jobs.%20As%20productivity%20rises%2C%20total%20economic%20output%20will%20increase%20and%20GDP%20will%20rise.%20This%20will%20create%20a%20virtuous%20cycle%2C%20as%20companies%20will%20need%20to%20expand%20operations%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20this%20increased%20demand%2C%20which%20means%20they%20will%20need%20more%20workers.%20Plus%2C%20labor-productivity%20growth%20has%20been%20shown%20to%20raise%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.mckinsey.com%2Fmgi%2Four-research%2Frekindling-us-productivity-for-a-new-era%23introduction%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereal%20incomes%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20benefiting%20workers%20and%20households.%20Simply%20put%3A%20Technological%20innovation%2C%20even%20as%20it%20may%20lead%20to%20worker%20displacement%2C%20will%20help%20workers%20in%20the%20long%20run.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nber.org%2Fsystem%2Ffiles%2Fworking_papers%2Fw30389%2Fw30389.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EA%20widely%20cited%20study%20by%20the%20economist%20David%20Autor%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20colleagues%20found%2060%25%20of%20workers%20today%20had%20jobs%20that%20did%20not%20exist%2080%20years%20ago%2C%20suggesting%20that%2085%25%20growth%20in%20employment%20was%20a%20result%20of%20technology%20innovation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EFuture%20proofing%20%E2%80%94%20faster%20and%20smarter%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThat's%20all%20great%20news%2C%20but%20the%20turbulence%20of%20the%20AI%20revolution%20can't%20be%20ignored.%20The%20rapid%20pace%20of%20AI%20advancement%20and%20adoption%20makes%20this%20shift%20markedly%20different%20from%20past%20industrial%20revolutions.%20It's%20not%20as%20simple%20as%20textile%20workers%20being%20replaced%20by%20mechanized%20looms%20%E2%80%94%20workforce%20transformations%20are%20happening%20to%20varying%20degrees%20across%20occupations.%20And%20this%20pace%20of%20change%20is%20bound%20to%20outrun%20any%20changes%20in%20education%20and%20workforce%20preparation%20designed%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20the%20tech.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmerica's%20already%20antiquated%20workforce%20education%20system%20already%20fails%20to%20address%20modern%20workers'%20needs%2C%20let%20alone%20what%20they%20may%20need%20as%20AI%20takes%20hold.%20Maria%20Flynn%2C%20the%20CEO%20of%20the%20Washington%20think%20tank%20Jobs%20for%20the%20Future%2C%20said%20the%20US%20was%20encumbered%20by%20a%20%26quot%3Bpatchwork%20of%20programs%20that%20don't%20blend%20into%20a%20nice-looking%20quilt.%26quot%3B%20In%20fact%2C%20there%20are%2043%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brookings.edu%2Farticles%2Fshould-the-federal-government-spend-more-on-workforce-development%2F%23%3A~%3Atext%3DFederal%2520Funding%2520for%2520Workforce%2520Education%2520and%2520Training%2520in%2520the%2520U.S.%2520is%2520Extremely%2520Low%26amp%3Btext%3DThe%2520core%2520programs%2520in%2520Titles%2Cin%2520federal%2520funding%2520per%2520year.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Efederal%20employment-training%20programs%3C%2Fa%3E%20whose%20total%20budget%20is%20%2420%20billion%2C%20or%20less%20than%200.1%25%20of%20US%20GDP.%20This%20is%20an%20alarmingly%20trivial%20amount%20for%20an%20economy%20of%20%2425%20trillion%20GDP%20and%20over%20150%20million%20workers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22raw%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdatawrapper.dwcdn.net%2FLbJMm%2F1%2F%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Total%20public%20spending%20on%20labor%20markets%5C%22%20data-external%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22450%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20ease%20the%20pain%20of%20the%20labor-market%20upheaval%2C%20the%20US%20needs%20to%20invest%20more%20in%20its%20workforce%20%E2%80%94%20and%20fast.%20One%20approach%20is%20to%20adopt%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdenmark.dk%2Fsociety-and-business%2Fthe-danish-labour-market%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EDenmark's%20model%20of%20job%20security%20and%20retraining%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20known%20as%20%26quot%3Bflexicurity.%26quot%3B%20The%20system%20helps%20avoid%20structural%20unemployment%20by%20making%20it%20easy%20for%20employers%20to%20let%20go%20of%20workers%20and%20by%20providing%20a%20substantial%20cushion%20for%20those%20laid%20off.%20The%20program%20provides%20unemployment%20benefits%20for%20two%20years%20at%20as%20much%20as%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fec.europa.eu%2Fsocial%2Fmain.jsp%3FcatId%3D1107%26langId%3Den%26intPageId%3D4496%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%242%2C860%20a%20month%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20people%20who%20are%20laid%20off%2C%20as%20well%20as%20one-on-one%20job%20counseling%20with%20retraining%20opportunities.%20As%20a%20result%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwol.iza.org%2Farticles%2Fthe-danish-labor-market%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ethe%20Danes%20are%20unemployed%20for%20much%20less%20time%3C%2Fa%3E%20compared%20with%20workers%20in%20similar%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20once%20had%20a%20similar%20program%2C%20the%20Trade%20Adjustment%20Assistance%20program%2C%20which%20was%20established%20in%201974%20and%20administered%20by%20the%20Department%20of%20Labor%20for%20workers%20affected%20by%20trade%20and%20production%20in%20other%20countries.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20an%20entitlement%20program%20so%20that%20any%20worker%20who%20met%20certain%20conditions%20%E2%80%94%20that%20their%20job%20was%20displaced%20due%20to%20trade%20%E2%80%94%20had%20an%20entitlement%20to%20receive%20a%20package%20of%20income%20support%20and%20retraining%20support%2C%26quot%3B%20Flynn%20told%20me.%20An%20expansive%20and%20well-funded%20program%20geared%20toward%20the%20AI%20labor-market%20shift%20would%20help%20ease%20turbulence%20for%20workers%20by%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.brookings.edu%2Farticles%2Fmaladjusted-its-time-to-reimagine-economic-adjustment-programs%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eproviding%20relocation%20grants%20and%20wage%20insurance%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20temporarily%20bridge%20the%20wage%20gap%20when%20workers%20find%20employment%20in%20lower-paying%20jobs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20retrain%20people%20for%20an%20AI-based%20economy%2C%20the%20US%20could%20look%20to%20Singapore.%20There%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.skillsfuture.gov.sg%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eworkers%20above%20the%20age%20of%2025%20are%20given%20%24500%20in%20credits%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20access%2024%2C000%20courses%20in%20anything%20from%20data%20science%20to%20business%2C%20and%20a%20public-private%20retraining%20program%20makes%20sure%20skills%20training%20is%20matched%20to%20employers'%20job%20classifications.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fasia.nikkei.com%2FBusiness%2FTechnology%2FSingapore-seeks-to-stay-competitive-by-retraining-entire-workforce%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EEvery%20year%2C%20over%20660%2C000%3C%2Fa%3E%20people%20make%20use%20of%20the%20country's%20national%20retraining%20program.%20For%20those%20concerned%20about%20productivity%20lags%2C%20these%20kinds%20of%20large-scale%20upgrades%20to%20education%20and%20training%20have%20the%20potential%20to%20fill%20in%20the%20gaps%20of%20a%20major%20workforce%20transition.%20Singapore's%20efforts%20have%20helped%20step%20up%20the%20annual%20labor-productivity%20growth%20rate%20to%20a%20respectable%203%25.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAll%20these%20public-sector%20policies%20would%20still%20need%20to%20be%20complemented%20by%20private-sector%20investment%20in%20retraining.%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmitsloan.mit.edu%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2F2022-03%2FResults%2520of%2520a%2520New%2520National%2520Survey.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EIn%20an%20MIT%20survey%20of%20workers%2C%2050%25%20of%20respondents%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported%20receiving%20formal%20skills%20training%20by%20their%20employers.%20Incentivizing%20retraining%20through%20tax%20credits%20%E2%80%93%E2%80%93%20such%20as%20those%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tax.ny.gov%2Fpit%2Fcredits%2Femployee_training_incentive_credit.htm%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ENew%20York%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.georgia.org%2Fretraining-tax-credit%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EGeorgia%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%E2%80%93%20could%20spur%20employers%20into%20action%20and%20ensure%20everyone%20is%20ready%20for%20the%20AI%20revolution.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETechnology%20can't%20be%20uninvented%20%E2%80%94%20disruptive%20catalysts%20such%20as%20AI%20require%20the%20proactive%20pursuit%20of%20adapting%20to%20that%20change.%20And%20making%20workers%20resilient%20to%20large%20shocks%20requires%20recognizing%20that%20this%20technological%20wave%20can%20temporarily%20wipe%20out%20a%20large%20portion%20of%20the%20workforce%2C%20or%20it%20can%20be%20smoothly%20s