ve%20from%20the%20party%20to%20not%20support%20the%20move.%20NPP%20MLA%20from%20Tabudi%20constituency%2C%20N.%20Kayisii%2C%20was%20also%20the%20only%20one%20among%20his%20party%E2%80%99s%20seven%20MLAs%20to%20not%20support%20this%20move.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20development%20took%20place%20on%20August%208%2C%20after%20a%20meeting%20of%2040%20Manipur%20MLAs%20in%20New%20Delhi.%20In%20the%20light%20of%20this%2C%20there%20is%20strong%20likelihood%20that%20a%20resolution%20will%20be%20moved%20at%20the%20August%2021%20special%20session%20of%20the%20assembly%20by%20the%20Biren%20Singh%20government%2C%20which%20will%20seek%20to%20maintain%20the%20territorial%20integrity%20of%20the%20state.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20In%20other%20words%2C%20the%20statehood%20or%20Union%20Territory%20demand%20of%20the%20Kuki%20leaders%2C%20which%20is%20being%20supported%20by%20all%2010%20MLAs%20from%20the%20community%20across%20party%20lines%2C%20will%20be%20met%20with%20a%20clear%20%E2%80%98no%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPowerful%20Meitei%20civil%20society%20organisations%20like%20COCOMI%20have%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fmanipur-as-violence-rages-on-mlas-divided-over-whether-or-not-to-hold-special-assembly-session%5C%22%3Edemanding%3C%2Fa%3E%20such%20a%20resolution%20on%20territorial%20integrity%20for%20some%20time%20now.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20eight%20MLAs%20include%20NPF%20president%20Awangbou%20Newmai%2C%20also%20a%20minister%20in%20the%20Biren%20Singh%20government.%20On%20August%209%2C%20the%20eight%20had%20been%20among%20the%2040%20MLAs%20who%20had%20submitted%20a%20memorandum%20to%3Cspan%3E%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi.%20This%20was%20a%20day%20after%20the%20meeting%20of%20all%20the%2040%20MLAs%20in%20Delhi.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20memorandum%20signed%20by%20the%20MLAs%20categorically%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20a%20most%20important%20point%20that%20must%20be%20made.%20A%20%E2%80%98separate%20administration%E2%80%99%20as%20demanded%20by%20the%20ITLF%2FKukis%20is%20absolutely%20unacceptable%20under%20any%20circumstances.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fspecial-days-before-mha-was-to-finalise-kuki-accord-not-supported-by-cm-violence-broke-out-in-manipur%5C%22%3ESpecial%3A%20Manipur%20Violence%20Broke%20Out%20Days%20Before%20MHA%20Was%20to%20Finalise%20Kuki%20Accord%20that%20CM%20Did%20Not%20Support%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20memorandum%20also%20categorically%20sought%20implementation%20of%20the%20National%20Register%20of%20Citizens%20(NRC)%20in%20Manipur%20and%20added%20that%20the%20collection%20of%20biometric%20data%20of%20immigrants%20from%20Myanmar%20has%20started%20in%20the%20state%20and%20it%20%E2%80%9Cshould%20be%20expanded%20and%20strengthened%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2040%20MLAs%20also%20reiterated%20the%20Biren%20Singh%20government%E2%80%99s%20earlier%20demand%20that%20the%20Union%20government%20withdraw%20the%20suspension%20of%20operations%20(SoO)%20agreement%20with%20Kuki%20armed%20groups%20%E2%80%9Cat%20the%20earliest%E2%80%9D%2C%20stating%20that%20they%20have%20violated%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20ground%20rules.%E2%80%9D%20The%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%2C%20currently%2C%20is%20in%20talks%20with%20the%20SoO%20groups%20and%20has%20recently%20extended%20the%20ceasefire%20agreement%20with%20them.%20On%20August%2017%2C%20the%20groups%20are%20to%20hold%20a%20meeting%20with%20MHA%20officials.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAside%20from%20Awangbou%2C%20the%20signatories%20among%20the%20Naga%20MLAs%20are%20his%20NPF%20colleague%20Khashim%20Vashum%2C%20who%20is%20also%20the%20state%20transport%20minister%2C%20Ram%20Muivah%20(MLA%20from%20Ukhul)%20and%20Leishiyo%20Keishing%20(Phungyar%20MLA).%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELosii%20Dikho%20who%20decided%20against%20attending%20the%20New%20Delhi%20meeting%2C%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20from%20Manipur%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20was%20contacted%20by%20my%20party%20colleagues%2C%20including%20my%20party%20president%2C%20to%20join%20them%20on%20the%20trip%20to%20New%20Delhi%20for%20the%20August%208%20meeting.%20I%20was%20not%20told%20what%20exactly%20was%20on%20the%20agenda.%20I%20told%20them%20I%20am%20not%20clear%20on%20what%20it%20is%20about.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDikho%20said%20that%20since%20the%20United%20Naga%20Council%20(UNC)%2C%20the%20apex%20body%20of%20Nagas%20in%20the%20state%2C%20was%20organising%20a%20rally%20in%20his%20home%20district%20of%20Senapati%2C%20he%20felt%20that%20he%20should%20rather%20join%20it%20as%20its%20purpose%20was%20to%20urge%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20find%20a%20solution%20to%20the%20Naga%20political%20question%20soon.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20date%20of%20the%20submission%20of%20the%20memorandum%20to%20the%20prime%20minister%20by%20the%20MLAs%20was%20significant%20as%20on%20the%20same%20day%2C%20the%20UNC%20too%20submitted%20a%20memorandum%20to%20Modi%2C%20urging%20him%20to%20sort%20out%20the%20Naga%20problem%2C%20and%20not%20touch%20the%20community%E2%80%99s%20traditional%20land%20while%20dealing%20with%20any%20other%20community%E2%80%99s%20political%20movement.%20Earlier%2C%20the%20UNC%20and%20the%20Naga%20Hoho%20had%20also%20issued%20press%20statements%20asking%20all%20the%20Naga%20MLAs%20of%20the%20Manipur%20assembly%2C%20across%20party%20lines%2C%20to%20not%20attend%20the%20session%20as%20they%20felt%20it%20was%20at%20the%20behest%20of%20Meitei%20civil%20society%20organisations.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENPF%20sources%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EWire%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20their%20party%20MLAs%2C%20led%20by%20the%20president%2C%20met%20the%20chief%20minister%20in%20Imphal%20in%20the%20first%20week%20of%20August.%20CM%20Biren%20asked%20them%20to%20travel%20to%20Delhi%20to%20sign%20on%20the%20memorandum%20rejecting%20the%20demand%20for%20a%20separate%20administration%20by%20Kuki%20leaders%2C%20including%20those%20from%20within%20the%20BJP.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20NPF%20entourage%20to%20Delhi%20was%20joined%20by%20the%20independent%20Naga%20MLA%20K.%20Jumo%20Sha%20and%20one%20other%20Naga%20MLA%2C%20Janghemlung%20Panmei.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPanmei%2C%20an%20MLA%20from%20another%20BJP%20ally%2C%20the%20NPP%2C%20was%20joining%20five%20other%20MLAs%20from%20the%20valley%20areas%20who%20belong%20to%20his%20party.%20However%2C%20his%20party%20colleague%20and%20fellow%20Naga%2C%20Tadubi%20MLA%20N.%20Kayisii%2C%20refused%20to%20be%20a%20part%20of%20it.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ES.%20S.%20Olish%2C%20an%20MLA%20from%20Chandel%20district%20seen%20as%20close%20to%20the%20chief%20minister%2C%20was%20also%20a%20signatory%20to%20the%20memorandum%20on%20August%209.%20Interestingly%2C%20most%20of%20the%20rebel%20MLAs%20of%20the%20BJP%20stayed%20away%20from%20the%20August%208%20meeting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECM%20Biren%20himself%20didn%E2%80%99t%20attend%20the%20August%208%20meeting%20in%20New%20Delhi%20but%20his%20son-in-law%20and%20BJP%20MLA%20R.K.%20Imo%20Singh%20did%20and%20signed%20on%20memorandum.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fspecial-controlling-manipur-matters-even-solutions-for-peace-risk-drawing-in-more-communities%5C%22%3ESpecial%20%7C%20Controlling%20Manipur%20Matters%3A%20Even%20Solutions%20for%20Peace%20Risk%20Drawing%20in%20More%20Communities%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMeanwhile%2C%20on%20coming%20to%20know%20about%20the%20Naga%20MLAs%E2%80%99%20support%20to%20the%20chief%20minister%E2%80%99s%20move%2C%20several%20Naga%20civil%20society%20bodies%20including%20the%20UNC%20came%20down%20heavily%20on%20them%20on%C2%A0August%2013.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnagalandpost.com%2Findex.php%2Func-disowns-representation-by-8-manipur-naga-mlas-to-pm%2F%5C%22%3EIn%20a%20statement%2C%20UNC%20particularly%20mentioned%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20MLAs%20chose%20not%20to%20attend%20the%20August%209%20rally%20called%20by%20it%20in%20the%20Naga-dominated%20districts%20of%20Manipur%20and%20instead%20went%20to%20New%20Delhi.%20UNC%20said%20their%20move%20%E2%80%9Cnegated%20the%20collective%20sentiments%20of%20the%20Naga%20populace%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20said%2C%20on%20a%20day%20when%20%E2%80%9Call%20Nagas%20(of%20Manipur)%20were%20out%20reiterating%20for%20an%20inclusive%2C%20acceptable%20and%20honourable%20solution%20Indi-Naga%20political%20issue%2C%E2%80%9D%20these%20eight%20MLAs%20were%20busy%20%E2%80%9Csubmitting%20representation%20with%20some%20contradictory%20demands%20to%20the%20prime%20minister%20of%20India%E2%80%9D%20which%20%E2%80%9Cwas%20highly%20uncalled%20for%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CTherefore%2C%20it%20feels%20necessitated%20to%20place%20on%20record%20that%20the%20Naga%20legislators%20who%20have%20appended%20their%20signatures%20(to%20the%20memorandum)%20do%20not%20carry%20the%20collective%20aspirations%20and%20sentiments%20of%20the%20Nagas%20and%20hence%20disowned%20their%20representation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20a%20press%20statement%20on%20August%2013%2C%20the%20Working%20Group%20for%20Naga%20Rights%20in%20Manipur%20said%20it%20was%20%E2%80%9Cpained%20and%20aghast%E2%80%9D%20at%20the%20move%20by%20the%20eight%20Naga%20MLAs.%20Calling%20it%20an%20%E2%80%9Cabrasive%20act%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20representative%20of%20the%20Nagas%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20working%20group%20said%20these%20MLAs%20%E2%80%9Chave%20chosen%20to%20bow%20down%20to%20the%20diktats%20of%20certain%20vested%20interests%20groups%20whose%20sole%20purpose%20has%20been%20to%20maintain%20the%20status%20quo%20in%20every%20respect%2C%20in%20the%20state%20of%20Manipur.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20failed%20to%20contact%20the%20NPF%20president%20who%20had%20signed%20on%20the%20memorandum%2C%20sources%20in%20the%20party%20said%20that%20following%20the%20largely%20negative%20reaction%20in%20Naga%20society%20to%20their%20August%209%20move%2C%20it%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20look%20like%20the%20MLAs%20will%20attend%20the%20special%20session%20of%20the%20assembly.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBefore%20leaving%20for%20the%20August%208%20meeting%20of%20the%20BJP%20with%20its%20allies%20in%20New%20Delhi%2C%20R.K.%20Imo%20Singh%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thesangaiexpress.com%2FEncyc%2F2023%2F8%2F9%2FIMPHAL-Aug-8While-requesting-all-legislators-who-raised-the-demand-for-separate-administration-to-attend-th.html%5C%22%3Ehad%20urged%3C%2Fa%3E%20all%20legislators%20of%20the%20state%20including%20those%20from%20his%20party%20and%20those%20who%20belong%20to%20the%20Kuki%20community%20who%20have%20demanded%20a%20separate%20administration%20for%20the%20Kukis%2C%20to%20attend%20the%20special%20session%20and%20express%20their%20thoughts%20on%20the%20floor%20of%20the%20assembly.%20He%20said%20all%20measures%20would%20be%20taken%20to%20ensure%20their%20safety%20and%20security%20in%20Imphal.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20pointing%20fingers%20at%20the%20former%20BJP%20ally%2C%20Kuki%20People%E2%80%99s%20Alliance%2C%20Singh%20had%20said%20since%20it%20withdrew%20support%20to%20the%20government%20and%20is%20also%20demanding%20separate%20administration%2C%20its%20MLAs%20should%20resign%20from%20the%20assembly.%20KPA%20has%20two%20MLAs%20in%20the%2060-member%20house.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692003777000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F20124144%2FF1SovOrXoAA5F5U.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmanipur-naga-mlas-biren-singh-kuki-separate-administration%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20special%20session%20of%20the%20Manipur%20assembly%20on%20August%2021%20is%20likely%20to%20see%20a%20resolution%20passed%20in%20favour%20of%20maintaining%20the%20state's%20territorial%20integrity.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fmanipur-naga-mlas-biren-singh-kuki-separate-administration%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Manipur's%208%20Naga%20MLAs%20Back%20CM%20Biren%20Singh's%20Move%20Against%20Kukis'%20Separate%20Administration%20Demand%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cb%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fb%3E%20Ahead%20of%20the%20crucial%20special%20session%20of%20the%20Manipur%20assembly%20on%20August%2021%2C%20eight%20Naga%20MLAs%20have%20backed%20chief%20minister%20N.%20Biren%20Singh%E2%80%99s%20move%20to%20press%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20not%20listen%20to%20the%20%E2%80%98separate%20administration%E2%80%99%20demand%20of%20the%20Kuki%20community%20following%20the%20brutal%20ethnic%20violence%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EOne%20of%20the%20eight%20Naga%20MLAs%20is%20K.%20Jumo%20Sha%2C%20an%20Independent%20from%20the%20Karong%20constituency.%20The%20rest%20are%20from%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%E2%80%99s%20allies%20in%20the%20National%20Democratic%20Alliance%20%E2%80%93%20the%20Naga%20People%E2%80%99s%20Front%20(NPF)%20and%20Nationalist%20People%E2%80%99s%20Party%20(NPP).%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Naga%20community%20has%2010%20MLAs%20across%20party%20lines%20in%20the%20state%20assembly.%20NPF%20MLA%20Losii%20Dikho%20was%20the%20sole%20legislator%20among%20the%20five%20from%20the%20party%20to%20not%20support%20the%20move.%20NPP%20MLA%20from%20Tabudi%20constituency%2C%20N.%20Kayisii%2C%20was%20also%20the%20only%20one%20among%20his%20party%E2%80%99s%20seven%20MLAs%20to%20not%20support%20this%20move.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20development%20took%20place%20on%20August%208%2C%20after%20a%20meeting%20of%2040%20Manipur%20MLAs%20in%20New%20Delhi.%20In%20the%20light%20of%20this%2C%20there%20is%20strong%20likelihood%20that%20a%20resolution%20will%20be%20moved%20at%20the%20August%2021%20special%20session%20of%20the%20assembly%20by%20the%20Biren%20Singh%20government%2C%20which%20will%20seek%20to%20maintain%20the%20territorial%20integrity%20of%20the%20state.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20In%20other%20words%2C%20the%20statehood%20or%20Union%20Territory%20demand%20of%20the%20Kuki%20leaders%2C%20which%20is%20being%20supported%20by%20all%2010%20MLAs%20from%20the%20community%20across%20party%20lines%2C%20will%20be%20met%20with%20a%20clear%20%E2%80%98no%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%20Such%20a%20resolution%20on%20maintaining%20territorial%20integrity%20of%20the%20state%20is%20being%20demanded%20from%20the%20government%20and%20the%20legislators%20by%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPowerful%20Meitei%20civil%20society%20organisations%20like%20COCOMI%20have%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fmanipur-as-violence-rages-on-mlas-divided-over-whether-or-not-to-hold-special-assembly-session%5C%22%3Edemanding%3C%2Fa%3E%20such%20a%20resolution%20on%20territorial%20integrity%20for%20some%20time%20now.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20eight%20MLAs%20include%20NPF%20president%20Awangbou%20Newmai%2C%20also%20a%20minister%20in%20the%20Biren%20Singh%20government.%20On%20August%209%2C%20the%20eight%20had%20submitted%20a%20memorandum%20to%3Cspan%3E%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi.%20This%20was%20a%20day%20after%20the%20meeting%20of%2040%20MLAs%20in%20Delhi.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20memorandum%20signed%20by%20the%20MLAs%20categorically%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20a%20most%20important%20point%20that%20must%20be%20made.%20A%20%E2%80%98separate%20administration%E2%80%99%20as%20demanded%20by%20the%20ITLF%2FKukis%20is%20absolutely%20unacceptable%20under%20any%20circumstances.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20memorandum%20also%20categorically%20sought%20implementation%20of%20the%20National%20Register%20of%20Citizens%20(NRC)%20in%20Manipur%20and%20added%20that%20the%20collection%20of%20biometric%20data%20of%20immigrants%20from%20Myanmar%20has%20started%20in%20the%20state%20and%20it%20%E2%80%9Cshould%20be%20expanded%20and%20strengthened%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2040%20MLAs%20also%20reiterated%20the%20Biren%20Singh%20government%E2%80%99s%20earlier%20demand%20that%20the%20Union%20government%20withdraw%20the%20suspension%20of%20operations%20(SoO)%20agreement%20with%20Kuki%20armed%20groups%20%E2%80%9Cat%20the%20earliest%E2%80%9D%2C%20stating%20that%20they%20have%20violated%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20ground%20rules.%E2%80%9D%20The%20Ministry%20of%20Home%20Affairs%2C%20currently%2C%20is%20in%20talks%20with%20the%20SoO%20groups%20and%20has%20recently%20extended%20the%20ceasefire%20agreement%20with%20them.%20On%20August%2017%2C%20the%20groups%20are%20to%20hold%20a%20meeting%20with%20MHA%20officials.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAside%20from%20Awangbou%2C%20the%20signatories%20among%20the%20Naga%20MLAs%20are%20his%20NPF%20colleague%20Khashim%20Vashum%2C%20who%20is%20also%20the%20state%20transport%20minister%2C%20Ram%20Muivah%20(MLA%20from%20Ukhul)%20and%20Leishiyo%20Keishing%20(Phungyar%20MLA).%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELosii%20Dikho%20who%20decided%20against%20attending%20the%20New%20Delhi%20meeting%2C%20told%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20from%20Manipur%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20was%20contacted%20by%20my%20party%20colleagues%2C%20including%20my%20party%20president%2C%20to%20join%20them%20on%20the%20trip%20to%20New%20Delhi%20for%20the%20August%208%20meeting.%20I%20was%20not%20told%20what%20exactly%20was%20on%20the%20agenda.%20I%20told%20them%20I%20am%20not%20clear%20on%20what%20it%20is%20about.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDikho%20said%20that%20since%20the%20United%20Naga%20Council%20(UNC)%2C%20the%20apex%20body%20of%20Nagas%20in%20the%20state%2C%20was%20organising%20a%20rally%20in%20his%20home%20district%20of%20Senapati%2C%20he%20felt%20that%20he%20should%20rather%20join%20it%20as%20its%20purpose%20was%20to%20urge%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20find%20a%20solution%20to%20the%20Naga%20political%20question%20soon.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20date%20of%20the%20submission%20of%20the%20memorandum%20to%20the%20prime%20minister%20by%20the%20MLAs%20was%20significant%20as%20on%20the%20same%20day%2C%20the%20UNC%20too%20submitted%20a%20memorandum%20to%20Modi%2C%20urging%20him%20to%20sort%20out%20the%20Naga%20problem%2C%20and%20not%20touch%20the%20community%E2%80%99s%20traditional%20land%20while%20dealing%20with%20any%20other%20community%E2%80%99s%20political%20movement.%20Earlier%2C%20the%20UNC%20and%20the%20Naga%20Hoho%20had%20also%20issued%20press%20statements%20asking%20all%20the%20Naga%20MLAs%20of%20the%20Manipur%20assembly%2C%20across%20party%20lines%2C%20to%20not%20attend%20the%20session%20as%20they%20felt%20it%20was%20at%20the%20behest%20of%20Meitei%20civil%20society%20organisations.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ENPF%20sources%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EWire%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20their%20party%20MLAs%2C%20led%20by%20the%20president%2C%20met%20the%20chief%20minister%20in%20Imphal%20in%20the%20first%20week%20of%20August.%20CM%20Biren%20asked%20them%20to%20travel%20to%20Delhi%20to%20sign%20on%20the%20memorandum%20rejecting%20the%20demand%20for%20a%20separate%20administration%20by%20Kuki%20leaders%2C%20including%20those%20from%20within%20the%20BJP.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20NPF%20entourage%20to%20Delhi%20was%20joined%20by%20the%20independent%20Naga%20MLA%20K.%20Jumo%20Sha%20and%20one%20other%20Naga%20MLA%2C%20Janghemlung%20Panmei.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPamei%2C%20an%20MLA%20from%20another%20BJP%20ally%2C%20the%20NPP%2C%20was%20joining%20five%20other%20MLAs%20from%20the%20valley%20areas%20who%20belong%20to%20his%20party.%20However%2C%20his%20party%20colleague%20and%20fellow%20Naga%2C%20Tadubi%20MLA%20N.%20Kayisii%2C%20refused%20to%20be%20a%20part%20of%20it.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ES.%20S.%20Olish%2C%20an%20MLA%20from%20Chandel%20district%20seen%20as%20close%20to%20the%20chief%20minister%2C%20was%20also%20a%20signatory%20to%20the%20memorandum%20on%20August%209.%20Interestingly%2C%20most%20of%20the%20rebel%20MLAs%20of%20the%20BJP%20stayed%20away%20from%20the%20August%208%20meeting.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECM%20Biren%20himself%20didn%E2%80%99t%20attend%20the%20August%208%20meeting%20in%20New%20Delhi%20but%20his%20son-in-law%20and%20BJP%20MLA%20R.K.%20Imo%20Singh%20did%20and%20signed%20on%20memorandum.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMeanwhile%2C%20on%20coming%20to%20know%20about%20the%20Naga%20MLAs%E2%80%99%20support%20to%20the%20chief%20minister%E2%80%99s%20move%2C%20several%20Naga%20civil%20society%20bodies%20including%20the%20UNC%20came%20down%20heavily%20on%20them%20on%C2%A0August%2013.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnagalandpost.com%2Findex.php%2Func-disowns-representation-by-8-manipur-naga-mlas-to-pm%2F%5C%22%3EIn%20a%20statement%2C%20UNC%20particularly%20mentioned%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20MLAs%20chose%20not%20to%20attend%20the%20August%209%20rally%20called%20by%20it%20in%20the%20Naga-dominated%20districts%20of%20Manipur%20and%20instead%20went%20to%20New%20Delhi.%20UNC%20said%20their%20move%20%E2%80%9Cnegated%20the%20collective%20sentiments%20of%20the%20Naga%20populace%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20said%2C%20on%20a%20day%20when%20%E2%80%9Call%20Nagas%20(of%20Manipur)%20were%20out%20reiterating%20for%20an%20inclusive%2C%20acceptable%20and%20honourable%20solution%20Indi-Naga%20political%20issue%2C%E2%80%9D%20these%20eight%20MLAs%20were%20busy%20%E2%80%9Csubmitting%20representation%20with%20some%20contradictory%20demands%20to%20the%20prime%20minister%20of%20India%E2%80%9D%20which%20%E2%80%9Cwas%20highly%20uncalled%20for%E2%80%9D.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CTherefore%2C%20it%20feels%20necessitated%20to%20place%20on%20record%20that%20the%20Naga%20legislators%20who%20have%20appended%20their%20signatures%20(to%20the%20memorandum)%20do%20not%20carry%20the%20collective%20aspirations%20and%20sentiments%20of%20the%20Nagas%20and%20hence%20disowned%20their%20representation.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20a%20press%20statement%20on%20August%2013%2C%20the%20Working%20Group%20for%20Naga%20Rights%20in%20Manipur%20said%20it%20was%20%E2%80%9Cpained%20and%20aghast%E2%80%9D%20at%20the%20move%20by%20the%20eight%20Naga%20MLAs.%20Calling%20it%20an%20%E2%80%9Cabrasive%20act%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cnot%20representative%20of%20the%20Nagas%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20working%20group%20said%20these%20MLAs%20%E2%80%9Chave%20chosen%20to%20bow%20down%20to%20the%20diktats%20of%20certain%20vested%20interests%20groups%20whose%20sole%20purpose%20has%20been%20to%20maintain%20the%20status%20quo%20in%20every%20respect%2C%20in%20the%20state%20of%20Manipur.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20failed%20to%20contact%20the%20NPF%20president%20who%20had%20signed%20on%20the%20memorandum%2C%20sources%20in%20the%20party%20said%20that%20following%20the%20largely%20negative%20reaction%20in%20Naga%20society%20to%20their%20August%209%20move%2C%20it%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20look%20like%20the%20MLAs%20will%20attend%20the%20special%20session%20of%20the%20assembly.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBefore%20leaving%20for%20the%20August%208%20meeting%20of%20the%20BJP%20with%20its%20allies%20in%20New%20Delhi%2C%20R.K.%20Imo%20Singh%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thesangaiexpress.com%2FEncyc%2F2023%2F8%2F9%2FIMPHAL-Aug-8While-requesting-all-legislators-who-raised-the-demand-for-separate-administration-to-attend-th.html%5C%22%3Ehad%20urged%3C%2Fa%3E%20all%20legislators%20of%20the%20state%20including%20those%20from%20his%20party%20and%20those%20who%20belong%20to%20the%20Kuki%20community%20who%20have%20demanded%20a%20separate%20administration%20for%20the%20Kukis%2C%20to%20attend%20the%20special%20session%20and%20express%20their%20thoughts%20on%20the%20floor%20of%20the%20assembly.%20He%20said%20all%20measures%20would%20be%20taken%20to%20ensure%20their%20safety%20and%20security%20in%20Imphal.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHowever%2C%20pointing%20fingers%20at%20the%20former%20BJP%20ally%2C%20Kuki%20People%E2%80%99s%20Alliance%2C%20Singh%20had%20said%20since%20it%20withdrew%20support%20to%20the%20government%20and%20is%20also%20demanding%20separate%20administration%2C%20its%20MLAs%20should%20resign%20from%20the%20assembly.%20KPA%20has%20two%20MLAs%20in%20the%2060-member%20house.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1692003777000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fmanipur-naga-mlas-biren-singh-kuki-separate-administration%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20special%20session%20of%20the%20Manipur%20assembly%20on%20August%2021%20is%20likely%20to%20see%20a%20resolution%20passed%20in%20favour%20of%20maintaining%20the%20state's%20territorial%20integrity.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fcommunalism%2Fmanipur-naga-mlas-biren-singh-kuki-separate-administration%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2