20Rajya%20Sabha%20MP%20Randeep%20Singh%20Surjewala%20said%20Shah%20had%20sought%20to%20lie%20and%20mislead%20the%20parliament%20by%20claiming%20that%20punishments%20for%20mob%20lynching%20and%20hate%20speech%20had%20been%20added%20to%20the%20new%20bill%2C%20reported%20%3Cem%3EDeccan%20Herald.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlready%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fhindi-imposition-modi-govts-nomenclature-for-new-criminal-law-bills-stirs-row%5C%22%3Emove%20to%20replace%20the%20three%20existing%20colonial-era%20criminal%20law%20codes%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20three%20new%20Bills%20is%20facing%20criticism%20from%20opposition%20parties%20due%20to%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20new%20Bills%20have%20Hindi%20names.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20three%20new%20bills%20are%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%20Bill%2C%202023%2C%20which%20will%20replace%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%2C%201860%3B%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nagarik%20Suraksha%20Sanhita%20Bill%2C%202023%20which%20will%20replace%20the%20Code%20of%20Criminal%20Procedure%2C%201898%3B%20and%20the%20Bharatiya%20Sakshya%20Bill%2C%202023%20which%20will%20replace%20the%20Indian%20Evidence%20Act%2C%201872.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20%3Cem%3EThe%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3EWire%3C%2Fem%3E%20had%20reported%2C%20while%20Shah%20said%20in%20parliament%20that%20the%20government%20will%20%E2%80%9Crepeal%20sedition%20completely%2C%E2%80%9D%20only%20the%20word%20has%20been%20removed%2C%20not%20the%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESurjewala%20has%20said%20that%20mob%20lynching%20was%20earlier%20covered%20under%20Section%20302%20(murder)%20of%20IPC%20in%20which%20death%20penalty%20or%20life%20imprisonment%20were%20the%20punishments.%20Now%2C%20Surjewala%20said%2C%20Shah%E2%80%99s%20government%20was%20giving%20huge%20%E2%80%9Cconcessions%E2%80%9D%20to%20those%20accused%20of%20lynching%20by%20watering%20down%20the%20lowest%20punishment%20to%20seven%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESurjewala%20also%20said%20that%20Shah%E